The paper deals with a graph problem related to social networks and resilience, which suggests categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem is NP-hard and involves removing vertices from a graph, which points towards categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper also investigates the parameterized complexity of the problem with respect to structural parameters of the input graph, which suggests category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
